messages:
Based on the task to return a list of colors, the draft-7 schema would look like this:

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "description": "A list of color names",
  "type": "array",
  "items": {
    "type": "string"
  }
}
```

This schema specifies that the data is an array where each item is a string, which in this context represents a color name.

instructions.draft-7:
Given the desired output from the instructions generate a draft-7 schema. Example: instructions: create a list of strings where each string is a method in the a bankaccount class draft-7 schema/output: {
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "description": "A list of method names for a BankAccount class",
  "type": "array",
  "items": {
    "type": "string"
  }
}
